The method spacePermissionManager.hasPermission will eventually try to get the user from embedded crowd, and the user cannot be found there. The user is still in user_mapping, so you'll get a user but without name, so crowd will fail. 

There are multiple points where a user being deleted from embedded crowd will cause an error in Team Calendars. Can we please find all instances where this can happen, and handle the failure gracefully?

h3. Workaround
Upgrading Confluence to 5.3 or above will fix some, if not all, of these user related NPEs. If that does not solve your issue, please contact [Support|http://support.atlassian.com].

